cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CV

The paper discusses the enhancement of video quality delivery in wireless networks, which involves communication schemes, mathematical modeling, and experimental techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with the impact of distortions on video transfer, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
